---
---

<section class="demo">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label section-label-bracket">Live Preview</div>
    <div class="section-title">Real signal,<br />ranked by intent</div>
    <p class="section-sub">Every post gets scored before it hits your inbox. Here's what a session looks like.</p>

    <div class="terminal">
      <div class="terminal-bar">
        <div class="terminal-bar-dots">
          <div class="terminal-bar-dot" style="background:#ff5f56"></div>
          <div class="terminal-bar-dot" style="background:#ffbd2e"></div>
          <div class="terminal-bar-dot" style="background:#27c93f"></div>
        </div>
        <span class="terminal-bar-title">leadecho &mdash; smart inbox</span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body">
        <div><span class="t-comment">// Scan completed &middot; 23 new mentions &middot; 3 scored as Leads Ready</span></div>
        <div class="t-sep"></div>

        <div><span class="t-label">&#9654; LEADS READY</span> <span class="t-dim">&middot; 3 mentions</span></div>
        <div style="margin: 10px 0 0 8px">
          <div>
            <span class="t-key">platform</span><span class="t-dim">:</span>
            <span class="t-str">reddit</span>
            <span class="t-dim">&middot;</span>
            <span class="t-key">intent</span><span class="t-dim">:</span>
            <span class="t-label">buy_signal</span>
            <span class="t-dim">&middot;</span>
            <span class="t-key">score</span><span class="t-dim">:</span>
            <span class="t-num">9.2</span>
          </div>
          <div style="color:var(--text2); margin: 3px 0 10px 0; font-size:0.78rem;">
            "I need something that monitors Reddit for mentions of my SaaS without hitting the API rate limits. Any recommendations? Budget: $50-100/mo"
          </div>

          <div>
            <span class="t-key">platform</span><span class="t-dim">:</span>
            <span class="t-str">twitter</span>
            <span class="t-dim">&middot;</span>
            <span class="t-key">intent</span><span class="t-dim">:</span>
            <span class="t-label">recommendation_ask</span>
            <span class="t-dim">&middot;</span>
            <span class="t-key">score</span><span class="t-dim">:</span>
            <span class="t-num">8.7</span>
          </div>
          <div style="color:var(--text2); margin: 3px 0 10px 0; font-size:0.78rem;">
            "anyone using social listening tools for B2B sales prospecting? tired of paying $200/mo for tools that don't actually find buyers"
          </div>

          <div>
            <span class="t-key">platform</span><span class="t-dim">:</span>
            <span class="t-str">hackernews</span>
            <span class="t-dim">&middot;</span>
            <span class="t-key">intent</span><span class="t-dim">:</span>
            <span class="t-label">complaint</span>
            <span class="t-dim">&middot;</span>
            <span class="t-key">score</span><span class="t-dim">:</span>
            <span class="t-num">8.1</span>
          </div>
          <div style="color:var(--text2); margin: 3px 0 4px 0; font-size:0.78rem;">
            "keyword alerts for Reddit give me 90% noise. I want something that actually understands what the person needs"
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="t-sep"></div>
        <div><span class="t-label">&#9654; WORTH WATCHING</span> <span class="t-dim">&middot; 8 mentions &middot; score 4.0&ndash;7.0</span></div>
        <div><span class="t-dim">&#9654; INFORMATIONAL</span> <span class="t-dim">&middot; 12 mentions &middot; auto-archived</span></div>
        <div class="t-sep"></div>
        <div><span class="t-comment">// AI draft ready for mention #1 &middot; approved replies in queue</span><span class="t-cursor"></span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
